uary 2020 events in Europe]]\n[[Category:2020 in Switzerland]]\n[[Category:March 2020 events in Europe]]\n", "text_old": "{{pp-protected|small=yes}}\n{{EngvarB|date=February 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{short description|Details of ongoing viral pandemic in Switzerland}}\n{{Current disaster|event=pandemic|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox pandemic\n| name = 2020 coronavirus pandemic in Switzerland\n| map1 = COVID-19 Outbreak Cases in Switzerland by Canton.svg\n| legend1 = {{center|Map of cantons in Switzerland by number of confirmed cases (as of 31 March)}} <ref name=\"Cases by Canton\">{{cite news|url=https://interactif.tdg.ch/2020/covid-19-carte-suisse/|title=Cas d'infection au Sars-CoV-2 en Suisse|date=18 March 2020|publisher=[[Tribune de Gen\u00e8ve]]|language=fr|access-date=19 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319122918/https://interactif.tdg.ch/2020/covid-19-carte-suisse/|archive-date=19 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> {{legend|#FFCECD|1-99 cases}} {{legend|#F28786|100-249 cases}} {{legend|#D42016|250-499 cases}} {{legend|#A31508|500-999 cases}} {{legend|#630800|1,000+ cases}}\n| map3 = \n| legend3 = \n| disease = [[COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain = [[SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location = [[Switzerland]]\n| first_case = [[Lugano]], [[Ticino]]\n| arrival_date = 25 February 2020<br />({{Age in years, months, weeks and days|month1=02|day1=25|year1=2020|month2=|day2=|year2=}})\n| origin = [[Wuhan]], [[Hubei]], [[China]] via [[Milan]], [[Italy]]\n| recovery_cases = 1,823<ref name=\"worldometers\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.worldometers.info/coronavirus/#countries|title=Confirmed Cases and Deaths by Country, Territory, or Conveyance|website=www.worldometers.info}}</ref>\n| deaths = 333<ref name=\"worldometers\"/><ref name=\"bag.admin.ch\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.bag.admin.ch/bag/en/home/krankheiten/ausbrueche-epidemien-pandemien/aktuelle-ausbrueche-epidemien/novel-cov/situation-schweiz-und-international.html |title=New coronavirus: Current situation \u2013 Switzerland and international |access-date=20 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320124233/https://www.bag.admin.ch/bag/en/home/krankheiten/ausbrueche-epidemien-pandemien/aktuelle-ausbrueche-epidemien/novel-cov/situation-schweiz-und-international.html |archive-date=20 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><br/>\n| confirmed_cases = 15,526<ref name=\"worldometers\"/><ref name=\"bag.admin.ch\"/>\n| website = [https://www.bag.admin.ch/bag/en/home/krankheiten/ausbrueche-epidemien-pandemien/aktuelle-ausbrueche-epidemien/novel-cov.html BAG Schweiz]\n}}\n\nThe [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]] was confirmed to have spread to [[Switzerland]] on 25 February 2020 when the first case of [[Coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]] was confirmed following a [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Italy|COVID-19 outbreak in Italy]]. A 70-year-old man in the Italian-speaking [[canton of Ticino]] which borders Italy, tested positive for SARS-CoV-2. The man had previously visited [[Milan]].<ref name=\"Switzerland_de22\">{{cite news|url=https://www.blick.ch/news/coronavirus-erster-bestaetigter-fall-von-coronavirus-in-der-schweiz-id15767285.html|title=Erster best\u00e4tigter Fall in der Schweiz|date=25 February 2020|publisher=[[Blick]]|language=de|access-date=29 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227232503/https://www.blick.ch/news/coronavirus-erster-bestaetigter-fall-von-coronavirus-in-der-schweiz-id15767285.html|archive-date=27 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"Switzerland_Ticinto2\">{{cite news|url=https://www.thelocal.ch/20200225/breaking|title=BREAKING: Switzerland confirms first case of coronavirus|date=25 February 2020|publisher=[[The Local]]|access-date=29 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227141321/https://www.thelocal.ch/20200225/breaking|archive-date=27 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Afterwards, multiple cases related to the Italy clusters were discovered in multiple cantons including [[Basel-City]], Z\u00fcrich and Graub\u00fcnden.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.swissinfo.ch/eng/politics/covid-19_switzerland-confirms-second-coronavirus-case/45582788|title=Coronavirus cases spreading in Switzerland|author=|website=[[Swissinfo]]|language=en|access-date=2020-02-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227084453/https://www.swissinfo.ch/eng/politics/covid-19_switzerland-confirms-second-coronavirus-case/45582788|archive-date=27 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gr.ch/DE/institutionen/verwaltung/djsg/ga/coronavirus/Seiten/Info.aspx|title=Informationen zum Coronavirus|website=www.gr.ch|access-date=2020-02-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227101110/https://www.gr.ch/DE/institutionen/verwaltung/djsg/ga/coronavirus/Seiten/Info.aspx|archive-date=27 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-swiss-idUSKCN20L167|title=Swiss coronavirus cases rise to nine as children placed in precautionary quarantine|date=2020-02-27|work=Reuters|access-date=2020-02-29|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200228072103/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-swiss-idUSKCN20L167|archive-date=28 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Multiple isolated cases not related to the Italy clusters were also subsequently confirmed.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://finance.yahoo.com/news/google-employee-zurich-office-tests-191438904.html|title=Google employee who was at Zurich office tests positive for coronavirus|website=finance.yahoo.com|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200228193637/https://finance.yahoo.com/news/google-employee-zurich-office-tests-191438904.html|archive-date=28 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 28 February, the national government, the [[Federal Council (Switzerland)|Federal Council]], banned all events with more than 1,000 participants. On 16 March, schools and most stores were closed nationwide, and on 20 March, all gatherings of more than five people in public spaces were banned. Additionally, the government gradually imposed restrictions on border crossings and announced economic support measures worth 40 billion Swiss francs.<ref>{{Cite news|last=NZZ-Redaktion|url=https://www.nzz.ch/schweiz/coronavirus-in-der-schweiz-die-neusten-entwicklungen-ld.1542664|title=Coronavirus in der Schweiz: die neusten Entwicklungen|work=Neue Z\u00fcrcher Zeitung|access-date=2020-03-20|language=de|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320161907/https://www.nzz.ch/schweiz/coronavirus-in-der-schweiz-die-neusten-entwicklungen-ld.1542664|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Timeline==\n[[File:BAG Plakat CoVi QR Abstand A3 297x420 d Poppler.svg|thumb|left|Official poster explaining hygiene rules and correct reaction in case of symptoms (version of 5 March 2020)]]\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic data/Switzerland medical cases chart}}\n\nOn 25 February 2020, [[Switzerland]] confirmed the first case of COVID-19, a 70-year-old man in the Italian-speaking [[canton of Ticino]] bordering Italy, who had previously visited Milan tested positive for SARS-CoV-2.<ref name=\"Switzerland\">{{cite news|url=https://www.dw.com/en/coronavirus-updates-us-criticizes-iran-and-china-over-the-their-handling-of-the-outbreak/a-52516885|title=Coronavirus updates: US criticizes Iran and China over the their handling of the outbreak|date=25 February 2020|publisher=[[Deutsche Welle]]|access-date=29 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200225161221/https://www.dw.com/en/coronavirus-updates-us-criticizes-iran-and-china-over-the-their-handling-of-the-outbreak/a-52516885|archive-date=25 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"Switzerland_de2\">{{cite news|url=https://www.blick.ch/news/coronavirus-erster-bestaetigter-fall-von-coronavirus-in-der-schweiz-id15767285.html|title=Erster best\u00e4tigter Fall in der Schweiz|language=de|date=25 February 2020|publisher=[[Blick]]|access-date=29 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227232503/https://www.blick.ch/news/coronavirus-erster-bestaetigter-fall-von-coronavirus-in-der-schweiz-id15767285.html|archive-date=27 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"Switzerland_Ticinto2\"/>\n\nOn 27 February, a 28-year-old IT worker from [[Geneva]], who had recently returned from Milan, tested positive and was admitted to the [[Geneva University Hospitals|Geneva University Hospital]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bag.admin.ch/bag/en/home/das-bag/aktuell/medienmitteilungen.msg-id-78268.html|title=New coronavirus Covid-19: three new confirmed cases in Switzerland|website=www.bag.admin.ch|access-date=2020-02-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227113237/https://www.bag.admin.ch/bag/en/home/das-bag/aktuell/medienmitteilungen.msg-id-78268.html|archive-date=27 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=SWI27.02.2020/> A 55-year-old Italian who worked in an international company also tested positive in Geneva.<ref name=\":21\">{{cite web|url=https://www.rts.ch/info/suisse/11127000-manifestations-d-ampleur-interdites-en-raison-du-coronavirus-conference-de-presse-du-conseil-federal-en-direct.html|title=Manifestations d'ampleur interdites en raison du coronavirus. Conf\u00e9rence de presse du Conseil f\u00e9d\u00e9ral en direct|language=fr|website=rts.ch|date=28 February 2020|access-date=28 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200228094931/https://www.rts.ch/info/suisse/11127000-manifestations-d-ampleur-interdites-en-raison-du-coronavirus-conference-de-presse-du-conseil-federal-en-direct.html|archive-date=28 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Two Italian children, who were on vacation in [[Canton of Grisons|Graub\u00fcnden]], tested positive and were hospitalised.<ref name=SWI27.02.2020>{{Cite web|url=https://www.swissinfo.ch/eng/politics/covid-19_switzerland-confirms-second-coronavirus-case/45582788|title=Switzerland confirms total of four coronavirus cases|author=|website=[[Swissinfo]]|language=en|access-date=2020-02-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227084453/https://www.swissinfo.ch/eng/politics/covid-19_switzerland-confirms-second-coronavirus-case/45582788|archive-date=27 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gr.ch/DE/institutionen/verwaltung/djsg/ga/coronavirus/Seiten/Info.aspx|title=Informationen zum Coronavirus|website=www.gr.ch|access-date=2020-02-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227101110/https://www.gr.ch/DE/institutionen/verwaltung/djsg/ga/coronavirus/Seiten/Info.aspx|archive-date=27 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=BielerTagblatt>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bielertagblatt.ch/nachrichten/schweiz/graubuenden-sagt-den-engadiner-skimarathon-ab|author=Swiss Telegraphic Agency|title=Graub\u00fcnden sagt den Engadiner Skimarathon ab|website=www.bielertagblatt.ch|language=de|access-date=2020-02-27|author-link=Swiss Telegraphic Agency|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227174547/https://www.bielertagblatt.ch/nachrichten/schweiz/graubuenden-sagt-den-engadiner-skimarathon-ab|archive-date=27 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nA 26-year-old man in [[Canton of Aargau|Aargau]], who had gone on a business trip the week before and stayed in [[Verona]], tested positive and was hospitalised.<ref name=SWI27.02.2020/> A 30-year-old woman, who had visited Milan, was admitted to a hospital in [[Z\u00fcrich|Zurich]].<ref name=\"SWI27.02.2020\"/> A 49-year-old man living in [[France]] and working in Vaud was confirmed positive in [[Vaud]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vd.ch/toutes-les-autorites/departements/departement-des-institutions-et-de-la-securite-dis/police-cantonale-vaudoise-polcant/medias/communiques-de-presse/news/12503i-coronavirus-premier-cas-detecte-dans-le-canton-de-vaud/|title=Coronavirus : premier cas d\u00e9tect\u00e9 dans le canton de Vaud|website=www.vd.ch|access-date=2020-02-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227213534/https://www.vd.ch/toutes-les-autorites/departements/departement-des-institutions-et-de-la-securite-dis/police-cantonale-vaudoise-polcant/medias/communiques-de-presse/news/12503i-coronavirus-premier-cas-detecte-dans-le-canton-de-vaud/|archive-date=27 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nA young woman, who had travelled to Milan, tested positive in [[Canton of Basel-Stadt|Basel-Stadt]]. She worked in a daycare centre in [[Riehen]], and after her test had been confirmed, the children at the daycare were put into a two-week quarantine.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-swiss-idUSKCN20L167|title=Swiss coronavirus cases rise to nine as children placed in precautionary quarantine|date=2020-02-27|work=Reuters|access-date=2020-02-28|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200228072103/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-swiss-idUSKCN20L167|archive-date=28 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> On 28 February, her partner, a 23-year-old man, also tested positive in [[Canton of Basel-Landschaft|Basel-Landschaft]].<ref name=\":21\" />\n\nOn 3 March, [[University of Zurich]] announced six confirmed cases of coronavirus at the Institute of Mathematics. As of 5 March, there are 10 confirmed cases at the University of Zurich, at least 7 at the I-Math and 1 at the Center of Dental Medicine.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.su.uzh.ch/en/Coronavirus.html|work=UZH|title=Coronavirus COVID-19|access-date=2020-03-03|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200303185246/https://www.su.uzh.ch/en/Coronavirus.html|archive-date=3 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 5 March, the [[Lausanne University Hospital]] announced that a 74-year-old female coronavirus case had died overnight.<ref name=\"vd.1\">{{Cite web | url=https://www.vd.ch/toutes-les-autorites/departements/departement-des-institutions-et-de-la-securite-dis/police-cantonale-vaudoise-polcant/medias/communiques-de-presse/news/12542i-coronavirus-ler-deces-dans-le-canton-de-vaud/ |title = Coronavirus : 1er d\u00e9c\u00e8s dans le canton de Vaud &#124; \u00c9tat de Vaud}}</ref> The patient had been hospitalised since 3 March, and had been suffering from chronic illness.<ref name=\"vd.1\"/>\n\nOn 11 March, a 54-year-old male died from COVID-19 in the [[Bruderholz]] Hospital in [[Canton of Basel-Landschaft|Basel-Landschaft]], marking the fourth fatal case in Switzerland. He had joined a religious event in [[Mulhouse]], [[France]] previous to contracting the virus and suffering from [[pneumonia]].<ref name=\"death4\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.20min.ch/schweiz/news/story/Coronavirus-News-Schweiz-29691128 |title=Berset-Challenge erreicht 1,4 Millionen Menschen |access-date=11 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200302111128/https://www.20min.ch/schweiz/news/story/Coronavirus-News-Schweiz-29691128 |archive-date=2 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n==Government response==\nOn 27 February, following the confirmation of COVID-19 cases in the region, [[Canton of Grisons|Graub\u00fcnden]] cancelled the [[Engadin Skimarathon|Engadine Skimarathon]].<ref name=BielerTagblatt/>\n\nOn 28 February, the Federal Council banned events involving more than 1000 people in an effort to curb the spread of the infection.<ref name=\"bag\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.bag.admin.ch/bag/en/home/krankheiten/ausbrueche-epidemien-pandemien/aktuelle-ausbrueche-epidemien/novel-cov.html |title=New coronavirus |access-date=3 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200302094217/https://www.bag.admin.ch/bag/en/home/krankheiten/ausbrueche-epidemien-pandemien/aktuelle-ausbrueche-epidemien/novel-cov.html |archive-date=2 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.admin.ch/gov/en/start/documentation/media-releases.msg-id-78289.html | title=Coronavirus: Federal Council bans large-scale events | access-date=29 February 2020 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200229141218/https://www.admin.ch/gov/en/start/documentation/media-releases.msg-id-78289.html | archive-date=29 February 2020 | url-status=live }}</ref> Multiple events such as carnivals and fairs were either postponed or cancelled. [[Geneva Motor Show]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.repubblica.it/motori/sezioni/attualita/2020/02/28/news/coronavirus_annullato_il_salone_dell_auto_di_ginevra-249789267/|title=Coronavirus, annullato il Salone dell'automobile di Ginevra|date=2020-02-28|website=la Repubblica|language=it|access-date=2020-02-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200229003901/https://www.repubblica.it/motori/sezioni/attualita/2020/02/28/news/coronavirus_annullato_il_salone_dell_auto_di_ginevra-249789267/|archive-date=29 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Baselworld]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.baselworld.com/en/news/news/2020-02-baselworld-communication|title=Baselworld postponed to January 2021|website=www.baselworld.com|language=en|access-date=2020-02-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200229072512/https://www.baselworld.com/en/news/news/2020-02-baselworld-communication|archive-date=29 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Bern Carnival and the [[Carnival of Basel]] were cancelled.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.swissinfo.ch/eng/politics/coronavirus_switzerland-bans-events-with-more-than-1-000-people/45585378|title=Switzerland bans major public events to slow spread of virus|author=|website=[[Swissinfo]]|language=en|access-date=2020-02-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200228234824/https://www.swissinfo.ch/eng/politics/coronavirus_switzerland-bans-events-with-more-than-1-000-people/45585378|archive-date=28 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> University of Bern replaced all face-to-face lectures with more than 250 attendees with online lectures.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.unibe.ch/coronavirus/index_ger.html|title=Coronavirus|date=2020-02-25|website=Portal|access-date=2020-02-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200229012228/https://www.unibe.ch/coronavirus/index_ger.html|archive-date=29 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 6 March 2020, the Federal Council announced a 'changed strategy' with a focus on the protection of the most vulnerable individuals, i.e., older persons and persons with pre-existing conditions.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.admin.ch/gov/de/start/dokumentation/medienmitteilungen.msg-id-78381.html |title=Coronavirus: Verst\u00e4rkter Schutz besonders gef\u00e4hrdeter Personen und Evaluation der wirtschaftlichen Auswirkungen |access-date=9 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200307144622/https://www.admin.ch/gov/de/start/dokumentation/medienmitteilungen.msg-id-78381.html |archive-date=7 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn 13 March 2020, the Federal Council decided to cancel classes in all educational establishments until 4 April 2020, and has banned all events (public or private) involving more than 100 people. It has also decided to partially close its borders and enacted border controls.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.lemessager.fr/6559/article/2020-03-13/coronavirus-la-suisse-ferme-aussi-ses-ecoles-et-renforce-le-controle-aux |title = Coronavirus : Il y aura des contr\u00f4les \u00e0 toutes les fronti\u00e8res suisses}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.lenouvelliste.ch/dossiers/coronavirus/articles/coronavirus-les-ecoles-fermees-dans-toute-la-suisse-les-reunions-de-plus-de-100-personnes-interdites-919189 |title = Coronavirus: Toutes les nouvelles du vendredi 13 mars}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.admin.ch/gov/de/start/dokumentation/medienmitteilungen.msg-id-78437.html |title=Bundesrat versch\u00e4rft Massnahmen gegen das Coronavirus zum Schutz der Gesundheit und unterst\u00fctzt betroffene Branchen |access-date=14 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200314134305/https://www.admin.ch/gov/de/start/dokumentation/medienmitteilungen.msg-id-78437.html |archive-date=14 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> The canton of Vaud took more drastic measures, prohibiting all public and private gatherings with more than 50 people, and closing its educational establishments until 30 April.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.24heures.ch/vaud-regions/eleves-maison-defi-teleenseignement/story/19330082 |title=Les \u00e9l\u00e8ves \u00e0 la maison, le d\u00e9fi du t\u00e9l\u00e9enseignement |newspaper=VQH |date=13 March 2020 |access-date=14 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200315052242/https://www.24heures.ch/vaud-regions/eleves-maison-defi-teleenseignement/story/19330082 |archive-date=15 March 2020 |url-status=live |last1=Collet |first1=C\u00e9cile }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.laliberte.ch/news-agence/detail/vaud-ferme-toutes-les-ecoles-du-canton/557223 |title = Vaud ferme toutes les \u00e9coles du canton}}</ref>\n\nOn 16 March 2020, the Federal Council announced<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fnuTzODXLvw |title=Archived copy |access-date=16 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318111106/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fnuTzODXLvw |archive-date=18 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> further measures, and a revised ordinance.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.bag.admin.ch/dam/bag/de/dokumente/mt/k-und-i/aktuelle-ausbrueche-pandemien/2019-nCoV/covid-19-verordnung-2.pdf.download.pdf/COVID-19-Verordnung-2.pdf |title=Archived copy |access-date=16 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317231248/https://www.bag.admin.ch/dam/bag/de/dokumente/mt/k-und-i/aktuelle-ausbrueche-pandemien/2019-nCoV/covid-19-verordnung-2.pdf.download.pdf/COVID-19-Verordnung-2.pdf |archive-date=17 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.bag.admin.ch/dam/bag/fr/dokumente/mt/k-und-i/aktuelle-ausbrueche-pandemien/2019-nCoV/covid-19-verordnung-2.pdf.download.pdf/COVID-19-Ordonnance-2.pdf |title=Archived copy |access-date=16 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317231246/https://www.bag.admin.ch/dam/bag/fr/dokumente/mt/k-und-i/aktuelle-ausbrueche-pandemien/2019-nCoV/covid-19-verordnung-2.pdf.download.pdf/COVID-19-Ordonnance-2.pdf |archive-date=17 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.bag.admin.ch/dam/bag/it/dokumente/mt/k-und-i/aktuelle-ausbrueche-pandemien/2019-nCoV/covid-19-verordnung-2.pdf.download.pdf/COVID-19-Ordinanza-2.pdf |title=Archived copy |access-date=16 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317231245/https://www.bag.admin.ch/dam/bag/it/dokumente/mt/k-und-i/aktuelle-ausbrueche-pandemien/2019-nCoV/covid-19-verordnung-2.pdf.download.pdf/COVID-19-Ordinanza-2.pdf |archive-date=17 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Measures include the closure of bars, shops and other gathering places until 19 April, but leaves open certain essentials, such as grocery stores, pharmacies, (a reduced) public transport and the postal service.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.bag.admin.ch/bag/en/home/krankheiten/ausbrueche-epidemien-pandemien/aktuelle-ausbrueche-epidemien/novel-cov/massnahmen-des-bundes.html |title=New coronavirus: Federal government measures |access-date=16 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200304142833/https://www.bag.admin.ch/bag/en/home/krankheiten/ausbrueche-epidemien-pandemien/aktuelle-ausbrueche-epidemien/novel-cov/massnahmen-des-bundes.html |archive-date=4 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nThe government announced a 42 billion rescue package for the economy, which includes money to replace lost wages for employed and self-employed people, short-term loans to businesses, delay for payments to the government, and support for cultural and sport organizations.<ref name=\"urlBund startet gr\u00f6sstes Rettungspaket der Schweizer Geschichte - Wirtschaft - tagesanzeiger.ch, tagesanzeiger.ch: Nichts verpassen\">{{cite news |url=https://www.tagesanzeiger.ch/wirtschaft/standardbund-startet-groesstes-rettungspaket-der-schweizer-geschichte/story/31151375 |title=Bund startet gr\u00f6sstes Rettungspaket der Schweizer Geschichte - Wirtschaft - tagesanzeiger.ch, tagesanzeiger.ch: Nichts verpassen |newspaper=Tages-Anzeiger |format= |accessdate=2020-03-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320202638/https://www.tagesanzeiger.ch/wirtschaft/standardbund-startet-groesstes-rettungspaket-der-schweizer-geschichte/story/31151375 |archive-date=20 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn March 20, the government announced that no lock down would be implemented, but all events or meetings over 5 people were prohibited. Economic activities would continue including construction.<ref name=\"urlEin Riesenpaket f\u00fcr die Wirtschaft, Einschr\u00e4nkung im Privaten - Schweiz: Standard - tagesanzeiger.ch, tagesanzeiger.ch: Nichts verpassen\">{{cite web |url=https://www.tagesanzeiger.ch/schweiz/standard/verhaengt-der-bundesrat-eine-ausgangssperre-ueber-das-land/story/23987451 |title=Ein Riesenpaket f\u00fcr die Wirtschaft, Einschr\u00e4nkung im Privaten - Schweiz: Standard - tagesanzeiger.ch, tagesanzeiger.ch: Nichts verpassen |format= |accessdate=2020-03-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320202644/https://www.tagesanzeiger.ch/schweiz/standard/verhaengt-der-bundesrat-eine-ausgangssperre-ueber-das-land/story/23987451 |archive-date=20 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn the weekend of the 27-29 of March the hackathon [https://codevscovid19.devpost.com/ #CodeVsCovid19]  was held, organised by ETHZurich with the support of the government. More than 2,500 coders from all over the world were united to device any imaginable plan to reduce the impact of the virus. Among the attendees, there were medical experts, scientists, programmers, economists, and many other backgrounds. A platform for [https://covid-self-report.ch/ self-reporting] was launched among the [https://codevscovid19.devpost.com/submissions hundreds of other projects].\n\n==Statistics==\n\nAs with most countries, the number of people actually infected with COVID-19 in Switzerland is likely to be much higher than the number of confirmed cases<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Lau|first=Hien|last2=Khosrawipour|first2=Veria|last3=Kocbach|first3=Piotr|last4=Mikolajczyk|first4=Agata|last5=Ichii|first5=Hirohito|last6=Schubert|first6=Justyna|last7=Bania|first7=Jacek|last8=Khosrawipour|first8=Tanja|date=2020-03-14|title=Internationally lost COVID-19 cases|url=http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S1684118220300736|journal=Journal of Microbiology, Immunology and Infection|language=en|doi=10.1016/j.jmii.2020.03.013|issn=1684-1182}}</ref>, especially as, since 6 March 2020, the Swiss government has had an official policy of not testing people with only mild symptoms<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.derbund.ch/schweiz/standard/bund-sucht-nicht-mehr-alle-coronainfizierten/story/20389898|title=Bund sucht nicht mehr alle Corona-Infizierten|work=Der Bund|access-date=2020-03-31|language=de|issn=0774-6156}}</ref>. \n\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic data/Switzerland medical cases}}\n\n{{Graph:Chart\n|type=line\n|linewidth=1\n|showSymbols=1\n|width=800\n|colors=#FF6347\n|showValues=\n|xAxisTitle=Date\n|xAxisAngle=-40\n|x=25 Feb, 26 Feb, 27 Feb, 28 Feb, 29 Feb, 1 Mar, 2 Mar, 3 Mar, 4 Mar, 5 Mar, 6 Mar, 7 Mar, 8 Mar, 9 Mar, 10 Mar, 11 Mar, 12 Mar, 13 Mar, 14 Mar, 15 Mar, 16 Mar, 17 Mar, 18 Mar, 19 Mar, 20 Mar, 21 Mar, 22 Mar, 23 Mar, 24 Mar, 25 Mar, 26 Mar, 27 Mar\n|yAxisTitle=No. of cases\n|y1= 2, 3, 8, 13, 18, 22, 40, 55, 72, 102, 198, 263, 328, 376, 505, 640, 880, 1223, 1530, 2153, 2327, 2650, 3815, 5118, 6427, 7385, 8160, 9395, 10117, 11217, 11801\n|y1Title=Confirmed cases\n|yGrid= |xGrid=\n}}\n\n{{Graph:Chart\n|width=800\n|colors=#F46D43\n|showValues=\n|xAxisTitle=Date\n|xAxisAngle=-40\n|type=rect\n|x= 25 Feb, 26 Feb, 27 Feb, 28 Feb, 29 Feb, 1 Mar, 2 Mar, 3 Mar, 4 Mar, 5 Mar, 6 Mar, 7 Mar, 8 Mar, 9 Mar, 10 Mar, 11 Mar, 12 Mar, 13 Mar, 14 Mar, 15 Mar, 16 Mar, 17 Mar, 18 Mar, 19