uca Cupido]], [[Hannes Daube]], [[Matthew Farmer]], [[Alex Bowen (water polo)|Alex Bowen]], [[Chancellor Ramirez]], [[Jesse Smith (water polo)|Jesse Smith]] <small>(C)</small>, [[Max Irving]], [[Drew Holland]] <small>(GK)</small>. Head coach: [[Dejan Udovi\u010di\u0107]].<ref name=\"2019WCH\"/>\n{{div col end}}\n\n====FINA World Cup====\n{{main|List of United States men's national water polo team rosters#FINA World Cup}}\n\n{{div col}}\n* {{flagicon|ESP}} [[1991 FINA Men's Water Polo World Cup|1991 Barcelona]] \u2013 '''{{Gold1}} Gold medal'''\n*: [[Jeffrey Campbell (water polo)|Jeff Campbell]], [[Michael Evans (water polo)|Mike Evans]], [[Erich Fischer (water polo)|Erich Fischer]], [[Charles Harris (water polo)|Charlie Harris]], [[Chris Humbert]], [[David Imbernino]], [[Douglas Kimbell|Doug Kimbell]], [[Craig Klass]], [[Robert Lynn (water polo)|Robert Lynn]], [[Kames Makshanoff]] <small>(GK)</small>, [[Terry Schroeder]] <small>(C)</small>, [[John Vargas (water polo)|John Vargas]], [[Craig Wilson (water polo)|Craig Wilson]] <small>(GK)</small>. Head coach: [[Bill Barnett (water polo)|Bill Barnett]].<ref name=\"HistoFINA\"/><ref name=\"HistoFINA PDF\"/>{{rp|37}}\n\n* {{flagicon|GRE}} [[1997 FINA Men's Water Polo World Cup|1997 Athens]] \u2013 '''{{Gold1}} Gold medal'''\n*: [[Gavin Arroyo]], [[Ryan Bailey (water polo)|Ryan Bailey]], [[Christopher Duplanty|Chris Duplanty]] <small>(GK)</small>, [[Dan Hackett]] <small>(GK)</small>, [[Chris Humbert]], [[Kyle Kopp]], [[Chi Kredel]], [[Jeremy Laster]], [[Drew Netherton]], [[Chris Oeding]], [[Brad Schumacher]], [[Peter Stern]], [[Wolf Wigo]]. Head coach: [[John Vargas (water polo)|John Vargas]].<ref name=\"HistoFINA\"/><ref name=\"HistoFINA PDF\"/>{{rp|37}}\n\n* {{flagicon|ROU}} [[2010 FINA Men's Water Polo World Cup|2010 Oradea]] \u2013 4th place\n*: [[Merrill Moses]] <small>(GK)</small>, [[Peter Varellas]], [[Mike Sharf]], [[Jeff Powers]], [[Adam Wright (water polo)|Adam Wright]], [[Jeff Tyrell]], [[Thomas Hopkins (water polo)|Thomas Hopkins]], [[Tony Azevedo]] <small>(C)</small>, [[Ryan Bailey (water polo)|Ryan Bailey]], [[Tim Hutten]], [[Jesse Smith (water polo)|Jesse Smith]], [[Tommy Corcoran (water polo)|Tommy Corcoran]], [[Andy Stevens (water polo)|Andy Stevens]] <small>(GK)</small>. Head coach: [[Terry Schroeder]].<ref name=\"2010WCup\"/>\n\n* {{flagicon|KAZ}} [[2014 FINA Men's Water Polo World Cup|2014 Almaty]] \u2013 4th place\n*: [[McQuin Baron]] <small>(GK)</small>, [[Conner Cleary]], [[Nolan McConnell]], [[Alex Obert]], [[Alex Bowen (water polo)|Alex Bowen]], [[Bret Bonanni]], [[Josh Samuels]], [[Michael Rosenthal (water polo)|Michael Rosenthal]], [[John Mann (water polo)|John Mann]], [[Luca Cupido]], [[Jesse Smith (water polo)|Jesse Smith]], [[Ryder Roberts]], [[Merrill Moses]] <small>(GK)</small>. Head coach: [[Dejan Udovi\u010di\u0107]].<ref name=\"2014WCup\"/>\n\n* {{flagicon|GER}} [[2018 FINA Men's Water Polo World Cup|2018 Berlin]] \u2013 6th place\n*: [[McQuin Baron]] <small>(GK)</small>, [[Johnny Hooper]], [[Dylan Woodhead]], [[Alex Obert]], [[Ben Hallock]], [[Luca Cupido]], [[Nic Carniglia]], [[Alex Roelse]], [[Alex Bowen (water polo)|Alex Bowen]], [[Ben Stevenson (water polo)|Ben Stevenson]], [[Jesse Smith (water polo)|Jesse Smith]] <small>(C)</small>, [[Max Irving]], [[Jack Turner (water polo)|Jack Turner]] <small>(GK)</small>. Head coach: [[Dejan Udovi\u010di\u0107]].\n{{div col end}}\n\n====Pan American Games====\n{{main|List of United States men's national water polo team rosters#Pan American Games}}\n\n{{div col}}\n* {{flagicon|BRA}} [[Water polo at the 2007 Pan American Games|2007 Rio de Janeiro]] \u2013 '''{{Gold1}} Gold medal'''\n*: [[Merrill Moses]] <small>(GK)</small>, [[Peter Varellas]], [[Peter Hudnut]], [[Jeff Powers]], [[Adam Wright (water polo)|Adam Wright]], [[Kevin Witt (water polo)|Kevin Witt]], [[Ryan Bailey (water polo)|Ryan Bailey]], [[Tony Azevedo]] <small>(C)</small>, [[Thomas Hopkins (water polo)|Thomas Hopkins]], [[Layne Beaubien]], [[Jesse Smith (water polo)|Jesse Smith]], [[John Mann (water polo)|John Mann]], [[Genai Kerr]] <small>(GK)</small>. Head coach: [[Terry Schroeder]].\n\n* {{flagicon|MEX}} [[Water polo at the 2011 Pan American Games|2011 Guadalajara]] \u2013 '''{{Gold1}} Gold medal'''\n*: [[Merrill Moses]] <small>(GK)</small>, [[Peter Varellas]], [[Peter Hudnut]], [[Jeff Powers]], [[Adam Wright (water polo)|Adam Wright]], [[Brian Alexander (water polo)|Brian Alexander]], [[Layne Beaubien]], [[Tony Azevedo]] <small>(C)</small>, [[Ryan Bailey (water polo)|Ryan Bailey]], [[Tim Hutten]], [[Jesse Smith (water polo)|Jesse Smith]], [[J. W. Krumpholz]], [[Chay Lapin]] <small>(GK)</small>. Head coach: [[Terry Schroeder]].\n\n* {{flagicon|CAN}} [[Water polo at the 2015 Pan American Games|2015 Toronto]] \u2013 '''{{Gold1}} Gold medal'''\n*: [[Merrill Moses]] <small>(GK)</small>, [[Nikola Vavi\u0107]], [[Alex Obert]], [[Jackson Kimbell]], [[Alex Roelse]], [[Luca Cupido]], [[Josh Samuels]], [[Tony Azevedo]] <small>(C)</small>, [[Alex Bowen (water polo)|Alex Bowen]], [[Bret Bonanni]], [[Jesse Smith (water polo)|Jesse Smith]], [[John Mann (water polo)|John Mann]], [[McQuin Baron]] <small>(GK)</small>. Head coach: [[Dejan Udovi\u010di\u0107]].\n\n* {{flagicon|PER}} [[Water polo at the 2019 Pan American Games|2019 Lima]] \u2013 '''{{Gold1}} Gold medal'''\n*: [[Alex Wolf (water polo)|Alex Wolf]] <small>(GK)</small>, [[Johnny Hooper]], [[Marko Vavic]], [[Alex Obert]], [[Ben Hallock]], [[Luca Cupido]], [[Hannes Daube]], [[Max Irving]], [[Alex Bowen (water polo)|Alex Bowen]], [[Chancellor Ramirez]], [[Jesse Smith (water polo)|Jesse Smith]] <small>(C)</small>. Head coach: [[Dejan Udovi\u010di\u0107]].<ref name=\"2019PAG\"/>\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Olympics statistics==\n{{main|United States men's Olympic water polo team statistics}}\n\n===Results by tournament===\n{{main|United States men's Olympic water polo team results}}\n\n{{United States men's Olympic water polo team results by tournament}}\n\n====Historica